97491.name: Life expectancy (Gapminder, UN)
97491.description:
Gapminder definition of life expectancy: The average number of years a newborn child would live if current mortality patterns were to stay the same. 

The UN Population Division defines life expectancy at birth as: The average number of years of life expected by a hypothetical cohort of individuals who would be subject during all their lives to the mortality rates of a given period.

Gapminder data is used up until 1949. UN Population Division (2017 Revision) data is used from 1950 to today.
